WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.140 --> 00:00:03.890
Microsoft Loop provides a platform for ideas and projects

1
00:00:03.890 --> 00:00:06.909
to keep planning and brainstorming all in one place.

2
00:00:07.690 --> 00:00:10.229
It is made up of 3 main features

3
00:00:10.800 --> 00:00:11.729
workspaces,

4
00:00:11.970 --> 00:00:16.299
these are a collection of pages which can be shared and generate ideas.

5
00:00:16.840 --> 00:00:17.729
Work pages,

6
00:00:17.930 --> 00:00:20.309
these make up main content within a workspace.

7
00:00:21.299 --> 00:00:22.329
And components,

8
00:00:22.620 --> 00:00:25.709
these are portable pieces of content that can be extracted and

9
00:00:25.709 --> 00:00:29.479
shared to other Microsoft platforms such as Teams and Outlook,

10
00:00:29.739 --> 00:00:32.380
but will still always automatically sync back to loop.

11
00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:37.200
You can access Microsoft Loop via any SharePoint homepage.

12
00:00:38.090 --> 00:00:41.349
You can also add and loop into your Microsoft Teams app

13
00:00:41.610 --> 00:00:45.990
by selecting the three dots icon and then searching loop and selecting.

14
00:00:46.650 --> 00:00:48.669
Right click on loop and select pin,

15
00:00:48.759 --> 00:00:52.090
and now you can access and use loop within your Teams app.

16
00:00:53.840 --> 00:00:55.250
To create a new workspace,

17
00:00:55.389 --> 00:00:57.889
simply select the plus icon in the top left

18
00:00:57.889 --> 00:01:01.470
menu bar and then select the option new workspace.

19
00:01:02.169 --> 00:01:03.049
For this example,

20
00:01:03.130 --> 00:01:08.190
we are going to create a new workspace called study to store notes and ideas.

21
00:01:08.730 --> 00:01:11.309
Type study where it says type a name,

22
00:01:11.849 --> 00:01:15.650
hover over the workspace image and then select update cover.

23
00:01:16.459 --> 00:01:20.449
Search and select one of the cover images available from the image library

24
00:01:20.669 --> 00:01:22.529
and then select update to save.

25
00:01:23.379 --> 00:01:26.040
You can also add an emoji icon if you wish.

26
00:01:27.089 --> 00:01:29.550
If you wanted to share this workspace with a colleague,

27
00:01:29.889 --> 00:01:33.029
you type their name into the share your space section and select.

28
00:01:34.029 --> 00:01:34.910
In this example,

29
00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:37.099
we will not be adding anybody else.

30
00:01:37.959 --> 00:01:39.029
Select create

31
00:01:39.940 --> 00:01:42.800
You will now be in the new workspace you just created.

32
00:01:43.709 --> 00:01:44.309
However,

33
00:01:44.519 --> 00:01:46.809
to click back to the homepage at any point,

34
00:01:46.900 --> 00:01:49.690
simply select the loop icon in the top left corner.

35
00:01:50.580 --> 00:01:54.000
You will now see your new workspace show up on your homepage.

36
00:01:54.900 --> 00:01:57.139
You can edit it at any time by selecting the

37
00:01:57.260 --> 00:02:00.269
three dots in the top right corner of the workspace

38
00:02:00.500 --> 00:02:03.160
and selecting the option to rename and style.

39
00:02:04.129 --> 00:02:08.250
Let's click back into our new workspace and explore some of its features.

40
00:02:09.080 --> 00:02:09.919
As a default,

41
00:02:10.130 --> 00:02:12.789
Loop will create a blank page for you to begin editing,

42
00:02:12.970 --> 00:02:13.529
however,

43
00:02:13.770 --> 00:02:16.070
you can choose any of the templates along the bottom

44
00:02:16.070 --> 00:02:18.889
of the page and then customise as you wish.

45
00:02:19.750 --> 00:02:24.050
Or you can also select template gallery to view more template options.

46
00:02:25.669 --> 00:02:28.229
All of these also have a cover image which you

47
00:02:28.229 --> 00:02:31.630
can customise by searching and selecting from the image library.

48
00:02:31.949 --> 00:02:35.490
This makes it easy to identify different pages within a workspace.

49
00:02:36.789 --> 00:02:39.130
You can also change the page icon.

50
00:02:40.800 --> 00:02:43.160
Any of the component sections can be edited,

51
00:02:43.410 --> 00:02:43.809
deleted,

52
00:02:43.889 --> 00:02:45.410
or you can add a new section.

53
00:02:46.949 --> 00:02:47.679
To delete,

54
00:02:47.839 --> 00:02:52.279
select the dots icon to the left of the component and select the option to delete.

55
00:02:53.339 --> 00:02:54.860
To add a new component,

56
00:02:55.190 --> 00:02:57.389
simply type the forward slash icon

57
00:02:57.509 --> 00:02:59.690
and it shows up all the options.

58
00:03:00.309 --> 00:03:02.460
Select the one that you want to insert,

59
00:03:02.580 --> 00:03:05.509
and it will add the component template into your work page.

60
00:03:06.869 --> 00:03:09.369
Let's add some checklists bullets as an example.

61
00:03:10.550 --> 00:03:13.479
Explore and have a go adding some of the other component

62
00:03:13.479 --> 00:03:16.059
templates to see what you can do with your page.

63
00:03:16.960 --> 00:03:21.529
The aim is to organise your information simply and effectively for best use.

64
00:03:23.960 --> 00:03:26.940
You can also add subpages within a main page.

65
00:03:27.779 --> 00:03:32.020
You will then see it show up underneath that page on the left-hand sidebar.

66
00:03:32.809 --> 00:03:36.089
You can select the main work page to go back to that page

67
00:03:36.250 --> 00:03:38.649
and to navigate easily within your pages.

68
00:03:39.570 --> 00:03:43.830
You can also insert other documents and data by selecting the plus icon

69
00:03:44.050 --> 00:03:46.470
and choosing the option to upload a file.

70
00:03:47.300 --> 00:03:50.639
You will now see it displayed within that page in the menu bar.

71
00:03:52.440 --> 00:03:55.419
Another option is you can add a link to a webpage,

72
00:03:55.639 --> 00:03:58.839
which will then show up within your workpage side menu bar.

73
00:04:01.369 --> 00:04:02.039
Lastly,

74
00:04:02.210 --> 00:04:04.410
you can add another workpage within this

75
00:04:04.410 --> 00:04:07.149
study workspace to keep everything organised.

76
00:04:08.009 --> 00:04:10.970
This way you can easily find what you need when you need it.

77
00:04:12.800 --> 00:04:17.160
The best thing about Microsoft Loop is that because it is part of Microsoft Office,

78
00:04:17.480 --> 00:04:21.720
it fully integrates with Microsoft Outlook and Microsoft Teams.

79
00:04:22.640 --> 00:04:23.510
For example,

80
00:04:23.709 --> 00:04:26.829
whenever you mention a person's name or assign them a task,

81
00:04:26.950 --> 00:04:28.829
they will get an Outlook notification

82
00:04:29.029 --> 00:04:30.670
which are linked to the work page

83
00:04:30.910 --> 00:04:34.070
as well as the task showing up in Microsoft Teams.

84
00:04:35.019 --> 00:04:39.619
So tasks assigned via Microsoft Loop can fully integrate into existing

85
00:04:39.619 --> 00:04:43.779
task-based systems you may already be using within Microsoft Teams.

86
00:04:44.760 --> 00:04:45.839
Thanks for watching.

87
00:04:46.079 --> 00:04:48.920
I hope this gives you confidence and some ideas for

88
00:04:48.920 --> 00:04:51.399
how you can make the most out of Microsoft Loop.